  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Scaling down doesn't work for Deployments in the following scenario:\n1. create a simple deployment with 5 replicas\n2. wait for rc/pods to be created and running\n3. update deployment, change the number of replicas to 1\n   result: the rc is never scaled down to 1, its size is 5 all the time.\n\nThe problems seems to be in scaleUp method:\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go#L234\nThis method should actually **scale down** the new rc, but it seems it doesn't due to condition in:\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go#L254\n(Please not that scaleDown method works only on old rcs, but there are no old rcs in our scenario).\n",
